    {
      "id": 351082,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Two conformations of <i>cis</i>-1,3-dimethylcyclobutane are shown. What is the difference between them, and which do you think is likely to be more stable?</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaElSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1413dc02d1f61e35e67f838176cc3ae5989b191e/OChem_04_04_005a.jpg\" alt=\"The ball and stick model of cis 1,3-dimethylcyclobutane. C1 is bonded to methyl at the top right. C3 is bonded to another methyl on the left.\">\n<b>(b)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaE1SIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--232ee8efc048065dce0a962d0caf83d7a38c328f/OChem_04_04_005b.jpg\" alt=\"The ball and stick model of cis 1,3-dimethylcyclobutane. C1 and C3 are each bonded to a methyl group at the bottom.\"></p>\n",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "Conformation <b>(a)</b> is more stable because the methyl groups are farther apart."
        }
      ],
      "community_solutions": []
    }
